{
  "stem": "7458.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I still remember a book he read to me that was seven or eight volumes, called [SPEAKING YIDDISH], the Don River.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And I remember him reading it to me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I also remember teaching me chess, how to play chess.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And to this day I enjoy chess because of my brother Meyer.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Oh, it was a wonderful thing to be a child in Jasionovka, the youngest of eight children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "By the time I was born, my oldest sister was ready to get married.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "In fact, my niece Roske, who now lives in Australia, is only three years younger than myself, so I became an uncle at age three.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And, of course, all of my older brothers and sisters, who had boyfriends and then husbands and wives, they thought I was a toy, so they played with me.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "They spoiled me rotten.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "I was probably the most spoiled child you have ever seen in your life, with eight brothers-- you know seven brothers and sisters and their boyfriends and spouses just believing that I could be played with like a toy.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "It was a very wonderful childhood.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And I think the security and the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] joy that I took with me from my childhood is what really managed to get me through the Holocaust and the difficult years that followed.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "I believe if I had not had that strength and that security, I probably would not have survived, because I wouldn't have had the-- what it took to go through the horrible things that followed.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that briefly gives you a picture of life in Jasionovka.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
